abstract_summ: Patients with moderately depressed GCS who do not trigger highest level activation are at risk for adverse outcomes . Time to first CT Head (CTH) was defined by time to first CTH after ED arrival: immediate (1 h) vs. delayed (1–6 h) Primary outcomes were time to neurosurgical intervention and time to ED discharge . Median GCS was 11 [10–12] in both groups and there was no difference in median Head AIS .
